# Keywords
- .csv: comma-separated values (spreadsheet)
- .Rmd: An RMD file (with the .Rmd extension) is a plain text file used in RStudio for data analysis and reporting. It combines standard text (written in Markdown), embedded executable code chunks, and output into a single, fully reproducible document.
- md: An .md file is a plain-text document saved in Markdown, a lightweight markup language used to format text for the web.
- Rproj: An .Rproj file is a configuration file used by the RStudio IDE to organize and manage your work as a "Project". 

